betterquesting:10.desc:8: Start by mining wood. You can use ore excavator to mine a large amount of wood quickly. The default key is 'Grave'.

So far you've been using some basic alchemy powder. This powder is inefficient and only gives you 75% of the item you are trying to construct which forces you to use more resources. I think its about time for an upgrade. With this advanced powder you'll be able to get 175% more from your alchemical endeavours. Use some reinforced stone, slime, and blaze to craft some.
You can extract water from leaves using a wooden extractor. This is a laborious process, so it would make sense to create an infinite water source as soon as possible.

Crush up a bunch of leaves (use wooden shears) or saplings into a ball. Plant matter works similarly to bone meal but is instant in most cases. Basic plant matter can also be transmuted into a number of other useful substances.
To be able to make clay, you need dirt. Until you can make dirt from plant matter in a combustion chamber you'll need to turn some of your precious grass blocks into dirt.
Fashion some planks into a rack. Use the rack to dry items out, like clay, or plant matter.
Hang some plant matter up to dry and you can get yourself a type of fertilizer called bone meal.

Grow some grass using your new found fertilizer. If you use your extractor to put water into the grass, you get yourself a soggy garden. Extract water out of it, and you'll have an arid garden. Both give different kinds of plants and crops. §c§nIn order to pick up the gardens themselves, use shears and HOLD SHIFT while mining with the shears!!!
Put some water into dirt using an extractor. Doing so will give you clay.
Drying clay on your drying rack will make a crude brick. There is little use to these, but you think you can mold it into a furnace.

It is recommended that you make a mob farm. This will allow you to kill creepers for gunpowder, skeletons for bones and zombies for rotten flesh. However, please note that this is not required. It will help you progress but there are ways to get around making a mob farm.
Craft a furnace

Using gunpowder and wood, you can make a contraption to combust items.

First make a casing, then make a combustion heater. Place the heater in the casing and surround the air block above the casing with 5 wooden planks. The uppermost plank can be replaced by a wooden trap door to more easily allow access to the enclosed space.

Fuel must be placed in the combustion chamber and the ingredients to be combusted in the air space above it. Place a button on the casing with the heater and press it to activate the device. Fire in the hole!
Smelt that clay to make actual bricks instead of that cruddy stuff you were making earlier. You can use this to make a crucible.

Enhance your basic fertilizer with colors to make it magical. Now magical flowers with special petals will grow when you use it on grass. Find a couple of these flowers that are white and pluck their petals. Attach them to a sappling to make it magical!
Place logs around your pure daisy. It will infuse them with magic. You can hammer these into a pulp with charcoal to get gunpowder.
Your magical flower can also turn water into §mwine§r snow. Collect some and make a freezer to store your cold beverages.
You can make some coarse dirt by compressing a bunch of snow and then freezing it solid. This coarse dirt can be turned into normal dirt by the application of a little elbow grease with a hoe.
Freeze some grass to get a frozen garden.

Use your new combustion chamber to turn gunpowder into a more combustible material known as blaze powder. You can condense this into a block. Then if you heat it up with a torch or other heat source it will create lava. Make sure you have a ceramic bucket or that your blaze block is placed in exactly the spot you want.
You can make a cobble generator using your lava, but you can also make a rock grinder tool and turn that cobble into gravel and that gravel into sand.
Upgrade your combustion setup using stone. This will allow for more heat to be stored in the multiblock and allow for more complex recipes to be executed.
Turning wood directly into charcoal is beyond your current technology level. For now, you'll need to cook plant matter in your furnace for all your charcoal needs.
If you grind out gravel you can find lots of flint. Flint is harder than stone and can be combined with wool and string to make a protective lattice.
Get Cactus. Pluck Cactus. Stick Cactus needle into sand. Hurt yourself.
Doing some special infüsion stuff you can turn grass into a jungle garden. You can also create magical mushrooms called nether wart to create helpful potions.
Through infüsion you can turn different types of bait into summoning items that summon the animal you want directly.
Using infüsion you can make a several useful trees. Rubber, Menril, Ghost, and Slime will all serve you during your journey.
Make some slime. Then use that slime to make some sap. It may be worth the investment to create a renewable source of these materials.
This upgraded combustion chamber can create a special kind of catalyst used in alchemy. Craft this and then make a table for your workings.

Combining gravel, sand, and clay in a stone combustion chamber results in a hard black brick that is heat resistant. You can use this to create a structure to melt down components and combine them to form alloys.

The strongest non-metal alloy. It takes 1 sand, 4 cobble, and 1 clay to get 6 ingots of this stone. In order to cast it, you will have to melt down these materials in the smeltery. Then pour the mixture onto fired clay allowing the reinforced stone to take a standard shape, such as a block or ingot.
§9§nhttp://bfy.tw/Fivo
Freeze a bone block to get a stable foundation to perform complex alchemical infusions.
Put some snow in a smeltery to get water. Put some blaze powder blocks in a smeltery to get lava. Ba-da-boom. You got obsidian.
The dimension you are sensing is solid and abundant with resources and life. Construct the 3 aspects of this dimension. Essence of Day, Essence of Night, and a bucket of the sky!

No, these aren't real diamonds. But at least they look like real diamonds. §c(When crafting these I §lstrongly §r§crecommend using the second tier alchemy catalyst! The lower tier one has 75% efficiency!)
Create a powerful symbol to channel alchemical energy. Use your Pure Daisy to purify the creation. You are making good progress...
Man, these fake diamonds sure feel real. Maybe the game won't notice that you're using fake diamonds when you put them in the enchantment table recipe...
With your new found alchemical infusion, you can create some more plants! This time, with the power of the wind.
You can use this new alloy to create strong and sturdy casings. These can be used to make lots of more complex and powerful machines.
By infusing a block of reinforced stone with lava, we can make a pillar that harnesses alchemical energy and transfers it along the pillar.
You can dig up dirt using a reinforced stone trowel and find worms. Worms are actually quite intelligent when compared to the dirt they live in.
You can create a controller for your alchemical device using a worm and some hooks.
You can create interfaces to place items and fluids into your alchemical machine and take them out.

You sense there is more to this modpack than just a trivial skyblock. Maybe an entire new dimension awaits... You feel as if you can combine the items that best represent this dimension you are dreaming of into a dimensional essence. Maybe you'll need two separate ones... Then you can make a complex alchemical structure to infuse this essence into a block that will warp you to this dimension. Sounds like a plan!
You did it! Your plan worked! Now to make your way to the next dimension... The Overworld... Place your blocks in a traditional nether portal fashion and then light the portal with a Worm (AA).
Ayyyyyyyy

Ghost wood has special properties that allow your reincarnates to re-form in the natural world around it. If you compress it a casing and put a binding agent in the center, you'll have yourself a respawn obelisk.
Using some catalyst, some magical plants, and some reinforced stone, you can make a magical cauldron. This cauldron can be filled with water and mixed with ingredients to make powerful effects.
Buckets can be made with reinforced stone if you hammer it together just right.

By mixing molten slime and molten glass, you can form a greenish glass that resonates with magical properties. Oddly enough, pouring this on top of coagulated blood (formed by standing in a smeltery and bleeding) turns it into a teleportation sphere known as an ender pearl. What an odd phenomenon.

With this new reinforced material, you think you can fashion together a highly advanced combustion chamber. Firstly, you can make a collector that only grabs the items that have combusted. Secondly, you can make a trap door to drop items into the chamber. This way you won't loose any heat and can make a lot of combustion items quickly without the hassle of breaking blocks or collecting items yourself.

In the overworld it is a §4§nbad idea§r to cave. There aren't lots of small veins of ores. Instead there are rare huge veins that contain hundreds of ores. In order to find these ores you'll need to test the soil to see if there is traces of ores beneath the surface. Make a prospector for magical materials.

In the overworld it is a §4§nbad idea§r to cave. There aren't lots of small veins of ores. Instead there are rare huge veins that contain hundreds of ores. In order to find these ores you'll need to test the soil to see if there is traces of ores beneath the surface. Make a prospector for technological metals.
This is a useful multiblock that turns coal into coal coke. Coal coke has double the burn time of coal and produces creosote oil as a bi-product.
Using alchemy, you can shatter some glass and use the shards to capture essence of the sky. Using these sky shards, you can melt them down in a crucible to get the liquid form of this essence.
A basic worktable provides a suitable surface for hammering ingredients.
From the sky, you are born...
You're cooking something up in the kitchen...
With technology, you rise...
No Description
It's a piece of cake to bake a pretty cake
Exploring to greater heights...
